6. EnCodec (Meta) — pretrained weights permanently excluded (FR-OP-32)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
Pretrained EnCodec weights (Meta / Facebook Research) are licensed under
CC-BY-NC 4.0 (non-commercial). Per FR-OP-32 (permanent constraint) and
docs/license-audit.md §3, no EnCodec weight file ships with Vokra's
official model zoo. The `mimi_rvq` op is codebook-shaped and could host
an EnCodec code path, but any EnCodec use requires the caller to bring
their own weight file and opt in through the M2-13 compliance research
flag (`VOKRA_ALLOW_RESEARCH_LICENSE=1` /
`CompliancePolicy::with_research_license(true)` /
`ComplianceLevel::Research`) — the runtime never loads them by default.
Release CI enforces the distribution-side exclusion via
`scripts/compliance/check-encodec-exclusion.sh`. Commercial codec
alternatives supported by Vokra: DAC (MIT), Mimi (CC-BY 4.0), WavTokenizer
(MIT), X-Codec 2 (MIT).

